This repository contains an Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) of the Sales Data Sample dataset. The purpose of this analysis is to understand sales trends, customer behavior, product performance, 
and revenue drivers across multiple countries.

What the Dataset contains:
The dataset contains transactional sales data with fields such as:
ORDERNUMBER
ORDERDATE
QUANTITYORDERED
PRICEEACH
SALES
PRODUCTLINE
STATUS
CUSTOMERNAME
COUNTRY
DEALSIZE

Important steps:
Perform data cleaning and preprocessing
Explore sales trends across time
Identify top-performing products and customers
Understand deal sizes and customer behavior
Analyze geographical revenue distribution
Identify correlations and revenue drivers

Data Cleaning Steps:
Converted ORDERDATE to datetime
Checked for missing values
Removed duplicates
Standardized column names
Created new features:
MONTH
YEAR
QUARTER
DAY_OF_WEEK

Key Visualisations:
Sales over time
Revenue by product line
Top 10 customers by revenue
Sales by country
Deal size distribution
Quantity vs Sales scatter plot
Correlation heatmap

Key Takeaways:
Insights Summary
Some product lines consistently outperform others
Certain countries generate more revenue despite fewer transactions
Deal size has a clear relationship with sales volume
Sales show visible monthly/seasonal patterns
Large purchase quantities show outliers that may indicate wholesale customers

